description: Master bedroom with ensuite bathroom (upstairs), and one bedroom downstairs (full bed), bath right outside room). 4-person max. We (host couple) will be away, but our one (quiet) housemate MAY be home. Beautiful, well-kept, and large, with all amenities. Guests have access to the kitchen, living room dining area, laundry room, and the garden, which are shared but lightly used by our one housemate (who will probably be home). Minimal. It's not that we are unfriendly, just very busy with work. (We teach.)  For breakfast, it's "help yourself." You'll have a sheet detailing the location of coffee, tea, types of milk in fridge, current stock of yogurts, granola, fruit, breads, etc. We love the natural beauty of the campus. We're walking distance to the Pogonip Trail, the Arboretum, the UCSC Farm, and fields and meadows, all great for exploring, running, or walking. Great town; beach is close (2.5 miles). Enjoy! Campus shuttle and city bus stops are near house. Dates September 1-17 are unhos

Newly renovated with modern decor. 5 minute drive to the beach. Located on the Upper West Side of Santa Cruz, this house is perfect for a quiet get-away.  Close to UCSC and multiple hiking trails.  Minutes to the redwoods or the Beach.  This home has a Queen bed, a dresser and a large closet in bedroom. Bathroom is equipped with blow dryer, shampoo/conditioner/soap and towels.  Washer/Dryer located on site.  Kitchen is fully stocked with dishes, coffee maker, coffee grinder, toaster, microwave, oven, range and refrigerator.  Flat screen T.V. , extended cable and free wi-fi also included. There is a lockbox located on the door. You will need to play a temporary parking permit on your dash during your stay.
